      "body" : "As this is a safety thing, I'm weakly inclined to NACK this based on the likelyhood that AcceptToMempool() will be called with an inappropriate max fee. Basically, you're taking the code that does that and splitting it in half, with one half duplicated.\r\n\r\nA better design might be to make a single function in the wallet that does the task of accepting a transaction: verifying sanity checks, then sending it via AcceptToMempool()",
